In this proclamation issued by President Donald J. Trump on April 30, 2018, he recognizes and celebrates the contributions of older Americans during Older Americans Month. He acknowledges that their care and dedication have made the country and communities strong, and their wisdom and guidance are valuable. The proclamation emphasizes the roles older Americans play in supporting their families and communities, working and volunteering, and mentoring future generations. The administration's focus is on protecting seniors from fraud and abuse, ensuring they receive Social Security benefits, improving healthcare, and lowering prescription drug prices. The proclamation calls for treating senior citizens with respect, meeting their needs, and allowing them to age with dignity. President Trump proclaims May 2018 as Older Americans Month and encourages all Americans to honor and care for older Americans throughout the year.